<br>
Allow me to explain in a nutshell:  Mark and I had a real dreamy vacation and we both came away from it with a renewed sense of love and companionship for each other.  We REALLY enjoyed spending time with each other.  <br>
So now the vacation is over and it's back to the old grindstone and Mark does not want go back to the way it was before we went on vacation.  He wants to continue the closeness we felt while we were on vacation.  To do this he wants me to stop playing EQ on weekends, inculding Friday.  The problem is that I had Friday nights as my commited EQ game night.  I liked Friday nights because I could play late without the fear of having to get up early for work the next day.<br>
<br>
He put it into a &quot;I should be more important than your game&quot; kinda situation.  He doesn't want me to quit, he just wants me to stop playing on the one night of the week that I look forward to, to &quot;get away&quot;.  He feels I should want to &quot;get away&quot; with him.  I just want a break from reaility but he doesn't seem to understand that.  He's taking it personally and I've tried very HARD to make him understand that I'm NOT choosing the game over him... But it certainly seems that way to him.  And that's because I would still be able to play Sun, Mon, Tues, Wed, and Thrus nights.  But its not the same... putting in piece-meal time like that (3 hours here, 4 hours there) really doesn't add up or get you anywere in this game.  And that's not to say that I'd get to play every one of those weekday nights, there are nights where I have Summer Session classes, other obligations to family and friends, maybe Mark may want to watch a new DVD with me or maybe I'll just be too tired from a day of work to play EQ.  SO we're looking at one or two weeknights a week I'll be playing total.<br>
<br>
What am I paying my $13.00 bucks for?<br>
<br>
What exactly is my problem?  I guess I just feel like I'm stuck between a rock and a hard place.  I honestly did/do enjoy our closeness.  I want to make him happy but I need to make me happy too.  I want both him and my gaming (in the capacity and times that I want them) but he makes me feel guilty that I want as much time to play EQ that I do.<br>
<br>
Is there a solution I'm not thinking of?  Is playing only two week-nights a week not so bad?  <br>
<br>
Am I doing myself a dis-service cutting down my EQ time when I really don't want to?  Am I a bad person for wanting to spend time on EQ when my husbear only wants to spend time with me?<br>
<br>
/shakes his head in confusion.<br>
 <p>Eric,<br>
