    First off, Glad you are back. You were missed!<br>
<br>
Now on to the meat of the matter. Most of you know my partner attempts playing EQ himself. I am one of those 4-5 hours a night players. One of the biggest reasons I can play that much is beacuse Mike does understand how important the game is to me. I make sure and make time for him. We've got several things planned for my upcoming time off, but a lot of it will be EQ as well. The big key yo all of this is Respect. Just as you respect Mark and give in to his wanting this or that, he should respect you enough to allow you to play EQ. Two nights a week? If that's what you two work out it's between you two. I know when Mike and I got into all this I pretty much set the rules that I would be playing hard core on weekends. I also know that I can set the rules with Mike a little easier than you can with Mark, but it's still about respect. If you collected stamps and dedicated so many hours a week to stamp collecting, would he have a problem with it? I know a lot of partners have issues with EQ because it's &quot;Just a silly video game&quot;. That only tells me they have no idea what EQ is. Maybe trying to show that part to Mark might help. Once Mike got the idea that when I log into EQ it's like hanging out with my buddies he got a lot easier about it. It wasn't so much that I was playing the game all the time, it was more spending time with my circle of friends, and the only way to do so is in Norrath. <br>
I hope I don't get too personal or step on any toes with this next few, but you put up with a lot from Mark. I don't see you being ungrateful or dissing him in anyway by asking that you be allowed to powerplay one night a week. If he wants Friday to be &quot;Couple's night&quot;, then have Saturday as a play day. Or sunday. It's give and take, and maybe you should ask him to give a little. I know my partner is more understanding than most, but I'm not exagerating to say that I wouldn't even be in a relationship that didn't allow me to do the things that I enjoy. A relationship is two individuals coming together on common ground, not one inviting the otehr to live the way they insist. As an Idividual, my partner has to understand that I play video games a lot. I also smoke, smoke pot, and like porn. All of those things have to be understood and dealt with. It's part of who I am. Yes, work on things with Mark, but to thine own self be true. Just tell him how important it is to you, not only on a game level, but on a socail level as well. I can only hope he'll understand and be a little more felxable than he has been. =)<br>
<br>
Good luck little cub. Not an easy one to be in.<br>
