<br>
While I've enjoyed the 3 years I've played, if I could go back now and not play, I probably would.  Why you ask, the biggest reason is the wedge it put between me and my ex.  He couldn't understand why I would rather sit in front of a computer on a gorgeous sunny day then go out and do something with him.  I think the last straw for him was when I woke up early on a saturday morning (like 7am, logged on and didn't log off until 4 am sunday night/mondy morning).<br>
<br>
After that, we started drifting farther and farther apart as he stopped asking me to do things.  I was so involved in the game that I didn't even realize that.  <br>
<br>
People will probably disagree with me on this, but as I've come to realize, alot of people use EQ as an escape from their lives.  Instead of dealing with the problems they have, they pour themselves into a fantasy based reality so they can hide away from the RL.  Once you have done that, its very hard to go back.  Plus, I've noticed that if you ever do fix what might be wrong in RL, the draw to log on EQ suddenly dimishes as you realize that you have other things.<br>
<br>
I've made the decision myself to completely quit.  No more going back for me as I will probably delete my characters and tear up the CD's.  Once that is done, I will never go back and I'll probably be the better for it.<br>
<br>
